#: src/introduction.md:1 src/operations/performance.md:7
msgid "Dora"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:3
msgid ""
"**Agentic Dataflow-Oriented Robotic Architecture** -- a 100% Rust framework "
"for building real-time robotics and AI applications."
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:5
msgid "Why Dora?"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:9
msgid ""
"**10-17x faster than ROS2 Python** -- 100% Rust internals with zero-copy "
"shared memory IPC for messages >4KB, flat latency from 4KB to 4MB payloads"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:10
msgid ""
"**Apache Arrow native** -- columnar memory format end-to-end with zero "
"serialization overhead; shared across all language bindings"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:11
msgid ""
"**Zenoh SHM data plane** -- nodes publish directly via Zenoh shared memory "
"for zero-copy data transfer; automatic network fallback for cross-machine"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:12
msgid ""
"**Non-blocking event loop** -- Zenoh publishes offloaded to drain task; "
"metrics collection runs in background"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:14
msgid "Developer Experience"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:16
msgid ""
"**Single CLI, full lifecycle** -- `dora run` for local dev, `dora "
"up/start` for distributed prod, plus build, logs, monitoring, record/replay "
"all from one tool"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:17
msgid ""
"**Declarative YAML dataflows** -- define pipelines as directed graphs, "
"connect nodes through typed inputs/outputs, optional [type "
"annotations](concepts/types.md) with static validation"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:18
msgid ""
"**Multi-language nodes** -- write nodes in Rust, Python, C, or C++ with "
"native APIs (not wrappers); mix languages freely in one dataflow"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:19
msgid ""
"**[Reusable modules](concepts/modules.md)** -- compose sub-graphs as "
"standalone YAML files with typed inputs/outputs, parameters, and nested "
"composition"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:20
msgid ""
"**Hot reload** -- live-reload Python operators without restarting the "
"dataflow"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:22
msgid "Production Readiness"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:24
msgid ""
"**Fault tolerance** -- per-node restart policies (never/on-failure/always), "
"exponential backoff, health monitoring, circuit breakers with configurable "
"input timeouts"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:25
msgid ""
"**Distributed by default** -- local shared memory between co-located nodes, "
"automatic [Zenoh](https://zenoh.io/) pub-sub for cross-machine "
"communication, SSH-based cluster management with label scheduling"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:26
msgid ""
"**Coordinator HA** -- persistent redb state store, daemon auto-reconnect, "
"dataflow state reconstruction on coordinator restart"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:27
msgid ""
"**Dynamic topology** -- add and remove nodes from running dataflows via CLI "
"without restarting"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:28
msgid ""
"**Configurable queue policies** -- `drop_oldest` (default) or `backpressure` "
"per input, with metrics on dropped messages"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:29
msgid ""
"**Soft real-time** -- optional `--rt` flag for mlockall + SCHED_FIFO; "
"per-node `cpu_affinity` pinning"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:30
msgid ""
"**OpenTelemetry** -- built-in structured logging with rotation/routing, "
"metrics, distributed tracing"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:32
msgid "Debugging and Observability"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:34
msgid ""
"**Record/replay** -- capture dataflow messages to `.adorec` files, replay "
"offline at any speed with node substitution"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:35
msgid ""
"**Topic inspection** -- `topic echo` to print live data, `topic hz` TUI for "
"frequency analysis, `topic info` for schema and bandwidth"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:36
msgid ""
"**Resource monitoring** -- `dora top` TUI showing per-node CPU, memory, "
"queue depth, network I/O across all machines"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:37
msgid ""
"**Log aggregation** -- subscribe to `dora/logs` to receive structured log "
"messages from all nodes without extra wiring"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:38
msgid ""
"**Trace inspection** -- `trace list` and `trace view` for viewing "
"coordinator spans without external infrastructure"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:40
msgid "Ecosystem"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:42
msgid ""
"**Communication patterns** -- built-in [service "
"(request/reply)](concepts/patterns.md), [action "
"(goal/feedback/result)](concepts/patterns.md), and [streaming "
"(session/segment/chunk)](concepts/patterns.md) patterns via well-known "
"metadata keys"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:43
msgid ""
"**ROS2 bridge** -- bidirectional interop with ROS2 topics, services, and "
"actions"
msgstr ""

#: src/introduction.md:44
msgid ""
"**In-process operators** -- lightweight functions that run inside a shared "
"runtime, avoiding per-node process overhead"
msgstr ""

