#: src/languages/c.md:175
msgid "Operator API (dora-operator-api-c)"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:177
msgid ""
"Headers: "
"[`apis/c/operator/operator_api.h`](../apis/c/operator/operator_api.h), "
"[`apis/c/operator/operator_types.h`](../apis/c/operator/operator_types.h) "
"Crate: `dora-operator-api-c`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:180
msgid ""
"The Operator API is used by shared libraries (`.so`/`.dylib`/`.dll`) loaded "
"into the Dora runtime process. Unlike nodes, operators do not have their "
"own `main` function. Instead, they export three functions that the runtime "
"calls at the appropriate lifecycle points."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:182
msgid ""
"The `operator_types.h` header is auto-generated by `safer-ffi` and defines "
"all C-compatible struct and enum types."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:184
msgid "Lifecycle Functions"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:186
msgid "`dora_init_operator`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:192
msgid ""
"Called once when the runtime loads the operator. Allocate and initialize any "
"operator state, then return it via the `operator_context` field. The runtime "
"passes this pointer back on every subsequent call."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:194
msgid "Return an `DoraInitResult_t` with `.result.error = NULL` on success."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:196
msgid "`dora_drop_operator`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:202
msgid ""
"Called once when the operator is being unloaded. Free all resources "
"associated with `operator_context`."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:204
msgid "Return an `DoraResult_t` with `.error = NULL` on success."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:206
msgid "Event Handling"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:208
msgid "`dora_on_event`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:218
msgid ""
"Called by the runtime each time an event arrives for this operator. Inspect "
"the `event` fields to determine the event type:"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:222
msgid "`event->input != NULL`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:222
msgid "New input available"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:223
msgid "`event->stop == true`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:223
msgid "Graceful shutdown requested"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:224
msgid "`event->error.ptr != NULL`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:224
msgid "An error occurred (UTF-8 string in `error.ptr`/`error.len`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:225
msgid "`event->input_closed.ptr != NULL`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:225
msgid ""
"An input stream closed (input ID in `input_closed.ptr`/`input_closed.len`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:227
msgid ""
"Use `send_output` to emit data to downstream nodes (see "
"`dora_send_operator_output`). Return an `OnEventResult_t` with the "
"appropriate `DoraStatus_t` to control the operator lifecycle."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:229
msgid "Input Reading"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:231 src/languages/c.md:272
msgid "`dora_read_input_id`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:237
msgid ""
"Returns a newly allocated null-terminated string containing the input ID. "
"The caller must free it with `dora_free_input_id`."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:239 src/languages/c.md:273
msgid "`dora_read_data`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:245
msgid ""
"Reads the input data as a byte array. Consumes the underlying Arrow array "
"from the input (the data can only be read once per event). Returns a "
"`Vec_uint8_t` with `.ptr = NULL` if the input has no data or the data has "
"already been consumed."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:247
msgid "The caller must free the returned data with `dora_free_data`."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:249
msgid "Output Sending"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:251
msgid "`dora_send_operator_output`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:262
msgid ""
"Sends output data to downstream subscribers. The `id` must be a "
"null-terminated string matching one of the operator's declared outputs. The "
"data (`data_ptr`/`data_len`) is converted to a UInt8 Arrow array internally."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:264
msgid "Returns an `DoraResult_t` with `.error = NULL` on success."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:266
msgid "Memory Management"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:268
msgid ""
"The Operator API allocates memory that the caller must free using the "
"corresponding functions:"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:270
msgid "Allocation source"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:270
msgid "Free function"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:272
msgid "`dora_free_input_id`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:273
msgid "`dora_free_data`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:280
msgid ""
"Failing to call these functions will leak memory. Do not use `free()` on "
"these allocations -- they are allocated by the Rust runtime and must be "
"freed through the API."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:282
msgid "Structs"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:284
msgid "`Vec_uint8_t`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:294
msgid ""
"A Rust-allocated byte vector. Access `len` bytes starting at `ptr`. Do not "
"modify `cap`. Free with `dora_free_data`."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:296
msgid "`DoraResult_t`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:300
msgid "// NULL on success, points to error string on failure\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:304
msgid ""
"Generic result type. A `NULL` error pointer indicates success. When "
"non-NULL, the error pointer contains a UTF-8 error message."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:306
msgid "`DoraInitResult_t`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:311
msgid "// opaque pointer to operator state\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:315
msgid ""
"Returned by `dora_init_operator`. On success, `result.error` is `NULL` and "
"`operator_context` holds the operator state pointer."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:317
msgid "`OnEventResult_t`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:326
msgid ""
"Returned by `dora_on_event`. Contains both an error/success result and a "
"status code controlling the operator lifecycle."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:328
msgid "`RawEvent_t`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:332
msgid "// non-NULL when this is an input event\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:333
msgid "// non-empty when an input stream closed\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:334
msgid "// true when shutdown is requested\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:335
msgid "// non-empty on error\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:339
msgid ""
"Represents an event delivered to the operator. Multiple fields may be set "
"simultaneously; check them in order of priority."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:341
msgid "`Input_t`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:344 src/languages/c.md:352
msgid "// opaque\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:347
msgid ""
"Opaque type representing an input event's data. Use `dora_read_input_id` "
"and `dora_read_data` to extract its contents."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:349
msgid "`Output_t`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:355
msgid ""
"Opaque type used internally by `dora_send_operator_output`. Not created "
"directly by user code."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:357
msgid "`SendOutput_t`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/c.md:365
msgid ""
"Callback handle passed to `dora_on_event`. Pass it to "
"`dora_send_operator_output` to emit data. Do not store it beyond the scope "
"of the current `dora_on_event` call."
msgstr ""

