#: src/operations/logging.md:1231
msgid "Performance Considerations"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1233
msgid ""
"Logging adds I/O overhead proportional to log volume. Here's how to tune it:"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1235
msgid ""
"**`min_log_level` is the most impactful setting.** It filters at the daemon "
"before any I/O: no log file write, no coordinator forwarding, no "
"`send_logs_as` routing. A node emitting 1000 debug lines/sec at "
"`min_log_level: info` generates zero overhead for those lines."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1237
msgid ""
"**`send_logs_as` adds a dataflow message per log line.** Each parsed log "
"entry is serialized to JSON, converted to Arrow, and sent through the "
"dataflow. For high-volume nodes, this can consume significant bandwidth. Use "
"`min_log_level` to limit what gets routed."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1239
msgid ""
"**`dora/logs` subscribers share a single serialization.** The daemon "
"converts each log line to Arrow once and clones the result for each "
"subscriber. The cost scales linearly with subscriber count, not log volume x "
"subscriber count. For most dataflows (1-3 log subscribers), this is "
"negligible."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1241
msgid ""
"**Log line size is capped at 1 MB.** Lines longer than 1 MB from node "
"stdout/stderr are truncated to prevent heap exhaustion. This protects "
"against buggy nodes that dump large binary data to stdout."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1243
msgid ""
"**Log file rotation is recommended for long-running dataflows.** Without "
"`max_log_size`, log files grow unbounded. A node emitting 100 lines/sec at "
"~200 bytes/line fills 1 GB in ~14 hours."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1245
msgid "**Recommended production settings:**"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1250 src/operations/distributed.md:457
#: src/operations/distributed.md:470 src/operations/distributed.md:483
#: src/operations/distributed.md:808
msgid "./my-node"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1251
msgid "info        # drop debug/trace at source\n    max_log_size"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1252
msgid "\"50MB\"       # rotate at 50MB\n    max_rotated_files"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1253
msgid "# keep 5 rotated files (300MB max)\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1258 src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:849
#: src/operations/distributed.md:828 src/advanced/ros2-bridge.md:863
msgid "Best Practices"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1260
msgid ""
"**Set `min_log_level` in production.** Source-level filtering at the daemon "
"prevents debug noise from reaching log files and the network. This is the "
"most effective way to reduce log volume since it filters before any I/O."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1262
msgid ""
"**Always set `max_log_size` for long-running dataflows.** Without rotation, "
"a single noisy node can fill the disk. Start with `\"50MB\"` (300MB total "
"per node with rotation) and adjust based on your storage budget. Use "
"`max_rotated_files` to tune how much history to keep (default 5, range "
"1-100)."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1264
msgid ""
"**Use environment variables for team defaults.** Set `DORA_LOG_LEVEL` and "
"`DORA_LOG_FORMAT` in your shell profile or CI configuration. Individual "
"developers can override with CLI flags."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1266
msgid ""
"**Use `--log-filter` during development.** Instead of changing YAML config, "
"use per-node display overrides to focus on the node you're debugging: "
"`--log-filter \"my-node=debug\"`."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1268
msgid ""
"**Use `send_logs_as` for operational monitoring.** Build monitoring nodes "
"that watch for error patterns, compute error rates, or forward alerts. This "
"keeps monitoring logic within the dataflow graph. Use `dora-log-utils` to "
"parse and format log entries in custom sink nodes (see "
"`examples/log-sink-file/` and `examples/log-sink-tcp/`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1270
msgid ""
"**Prefer `send_logs_as` over `send_stdout_as` for structured data.** "
"`send_stdout_as` captures every stdout line (including raw prints), while "
"`send_logs_as` only captures parsed structured log entries with full "
"metadata."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1272
msgid ""
"**Use `--local` for post-mortem debugging.** After a crash, `dora logs "
"--local --all-nodes` works without a running coordinator and merges all node "
"logs chronologically."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1274
msgid ""
"**Combine `--since` with `--grep` for targeted debugging.** Instead of "
"scrolling through thousands of lines, narrow the window: `dora logs --local "
"sensor --since 5m --grep \"error\"`."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1276
msgid ""
"**Use JSON format for log pipelines.** When feeding logs to external systems "
"(ELK, Grafana Loki, Datadog), use `--log-format json` for structured "
"ingestion."
msgstr ""

