msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:129
msgid "Configurable Health Check Interval"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:131
msgid ""
"The `health_check_interval` is a **dataflow-level** setting that controls "
"how often the daemon checks node health. Default is 5.0 seconds. Lower "
"values detect hung nodes faster but add more overhead. Set this at the top "
"level of your dataflow YAML, not per-node."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:133 src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:177
msgid "How It Works Internally"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:135
msgid ""
"The daemon runs a health check sweep at the configured "
"`health_check_interval` (via a tokio interval stream emitting "
"`Event::NodeHealthCheckInterval`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:137
msgid ""
"Each `RunningNode` has a `last_activity: Arc<AtomicU64>` field storing the "
"timestamp (milliseconds since epoch) of the last communication. This is "
"updated atomically by the node's communication handler "
"(`node_communication/mod.rs`) every time the node sends any request to the "
"daemon (event subscriptions, output sends, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:139
msgid ""
"The health check function (`check_node_health`) iterates all running nodes:"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:141
msgid "Skip nodes without `health_check_timeout` set"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:142
msgid "Skip nodes with `last_activity == 0` (not yet connected)"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:143
msgid "Compute `elapsed_ms = now - last_activity`"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:144
msgid "If `elapsed_ms > timeout_ms`, log a warning and **kill** the node process"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:146
msgid ""
"After killing, the normal exit handling runs, which evaluates the restart "
"policy. This means `health_check_timeout` combined with `restart_policy: "
"on-failure` automatically recovers hung nodes."
msgstr ""

