msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:171 src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:663
msgid "camera-node/frames"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:172
msgid "# seconds\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:175
msgid ""
"The `input_timeout` is set per input, not per node. Different inputs can "
"have different timeouts."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:179
msgid "The daemon maintains an `InputDeadline` for each input with a timeout:"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:181
msgid ""
"```\n"
"struct InputDeadline {\n"
"    timeout: Duration,        // configured timeout\n"
"    last_received: Instant,   // last time data arrived\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:188
msgid ""
"These are stored in `RunningDataflow.input_deadlines` keyed by `(NodeId, "
"DataId)`."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:190
msgid ""
"**Timeout detection** runs during the same 5-second health check interval. "
"The `check_input_timeouts` function:"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:192
msgid "Scans all `input_deadlines` entries"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:193
msgid "If `last_received.elapsed() > timeout`, the input is \"broken\""
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:194
msgid ""
"The `(node_id, input_id)` pair is moved from `input_deadlines` to "
"`broken_inputs`"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:195
msgid ""
"The daemon calls `break_input()` which sends `InputClosed { id }` to the "
"downstream node"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:196
msgid ""
"If all of a node's inputs are now closed (and none are broken/recoverable), "
"`AllInputsClosed` is sent and the node's restart is disabled"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:198
msgid ""
"**Deadline reset**: Every time data arrives on an input, its `last_received` "
"is reset to `Instant::now()`."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:200
msgid "Circuit Breaker: Auto-Recovery"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:202
msgid ""
"The circuit breaker tracks broken inputs in `RunningDataflow.broken_inputs`. "
"When new data arrives on a broken input:"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:204
msgid "The data is delivered to the node normally"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:205
msgid "The `broken_inputs` entry is removed"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:206
msgid "The input is re-added to `open_inputs`"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:207
msgid "A new `InputDeadline` is created (restarting the timeout)"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:208
msgid "An `InputRecovered { id }` event is sent to the node"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:209
msgid "The `circuit_breaker_recoveries` counter is incremented"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:211
msgid ""
"This means recovery is fully automatic. If the upstream node restarts (via "
"restart policy) and begins producing data again, downstream nodes seamlessly "
"resume receiving it."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:213
msgid "Node-Side Handling"
