msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:367
msgid ""
"By default the coordinator holds all state in memory. If the coordinator "
"process crashes or is restarted, all knowledge of running dataflows is lost "
"-- daemons continue running but become orphaned, and users must manually "
"re-run dataflows."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/fault-tolerance.md:369
msgid ""
"The **redb store backend** solves this by persisting coordinator state to a "
"single file on disk using [redb](https://docs.rs/redb), a pure-Rust embedded "
"key-value store with copy-on-write B-trees that are crash-safe by design."
msgstr ""

