#: src/operations/distributed.md:532
msgid "Auto-Recovery"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/distributed.md:534
msgid ""
"When a daemon disconnects and reconnects (e.g., after a network blip, "
"machine reboot, or service restart), the coordinator automatically re-spawns "
"any missing dataflows on that daemon."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/distributed.md:536
msgid "How it works"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/distributed.md:538
msgid ""
"Daemon reconnects and sends a `StatusReport` listing its currently running "
"dataflows."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/distributed.md:539
msgid ""
"Coordinator compares the report against its expected state (dataflows that "
"should have nodes on this daemon)."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/distributed.md:540
msgid ""
"For each running dataflow with nodes assigned to this daemon that the daemon "
"did not report, the coordinator sends a `SpawnDataflowNodes` command to "
"re-spawn the missing nodes."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/distributed.md:542
msgid "30-second backoff"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/distributed.md:544
msgid ""
"To prevent crash loops (e.g., a node that immediately crashes on spawn), "
"recovery uses a per-daemon, per-dataflow backoff:"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/distributed.md:546
msgid "After a recovery attempt, the coordinator records the timestamp."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/distributed.md:547
msgid ""
"Subsequent recovery for the same daemon/dataflow pair is skipped until 30 "
"seconds have elapsed."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/distributed.md:548
msgid "The backoff clears when the daemon reports the dataflow as running again."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/distributed.md:550
msgid ""
"This means a node that crashes immediately will only be re-spawned once "
"every 30 seconds, not in a tight loop."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/distributed.md:552
msgid "Limitations"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/distributed.md:554
msgid ""
"Auto-recovery only applies to dataflows started via `dora start` "
"(coordinator-managed). Local `dora run` dataflows are not tracked by the "
"coordinator."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/distributed.md:555
msgid ""
"Recovery re-spawns all nodes assigned to the reconnecting daemon, not "
"individual nodes. For per-node restart on crash, use [restart "
"policies](fault-tolerance.md#restart-policies)."
msgstr ""

