#: src/advanced/ros2-bridge.md:849
msgid "Limitations and Known Constraints"
msgstr ""

#: src/advanced/ros2-bridge.md:851
msgid ""
"**Action server auto-accept**: All incoming goals are automatically "
"accepted. The handler cannot reject goals before execution starts."
msgstr ""

#: src/advanced/ros2-bridge.md:852
msgid ""
"**No action cancel support**: Neither client nor server handles ROS2 cancel "
"requests."
msgstr ""

#: src/advanced/ros2-bridge.md:853
msgid ""
"**No `wait_for_action_server`**: The `ros2_client` library does not provide "
"this API. Start the action server before the dataflow. The first goal will "
"time out (30s) if the server is unavailable."
msgstr ""

#: src/advanced/ros2-bridge.md:854
msgid ""
"**Single-flight service client**: The service client processes requests "
"sequentially -- each request blocks until the response arrives (or times out "
"at 30s)."
msgstr ""

#: src/advanced/ros2-bridge.md:855
msgid ""
"**QoS uniform for service/action channels**: The `qos` config applies to all "
"service/action sub-channels (goal, result, cancel, feedback, status). "
"Per-channel QoS is not configurable."
msgstr ""

#: src/advanced/ros2-bridge.md:856
msgid ""
"**`AMENT_PREFIX_PATH` required**: The bridge fails at startup if no ROS2 "
"message definitions are found."
msgstr ""

#: src/advanced/ros2-bridge.md:857
msgid ""
"**Max 64 topics**: Multi-topic mode supports at most 64 topics per bridge "
"node."
msgstr ""

#: src/advanced/ros2-bridge.md:858
msgid ""
"**Max 8 concurrent action goals**: Additional goals receive `Aborted` status "
"when the limit is reached."
msgstr ""

#: src/advanced/ros2-bridge.md:859
msgid ""
"**Max 64 pending service requests (server)**: Requests are dropped when the "
"queue is full."
msgstr ""

#: src/advanced/ros2-bridge.md:865
msgid ""
"**Source your ROS2 environment before running.** Ensure `AMENT_PREFIX_PATH` "
"is set and includes all required message packages. The bridge logs an error "
"if no definitions are found."
msgstr ""

#: src/advanced/ros2-bridge.md:867
msgid ""
"**Start action servers before the dataflow.** There is no wait mechanism for "
"action servers. If the server is not ready, the first goal send will time "
"out after 30 seconds."
msgstr ""

#: src/advanced/ros2-bridge.md:869
msgid ""
"**Use multi-topic mode for related topics.** Bridging `/turtle1/pose` "
"(subscribe) and `/turtle1/cmd_vel` (publish) on the same bridge node reduces "
"resource usage compared to two separate bridge nodes."
msgstr ""

#: src/advanced/ros2-bridge.md:871
msgid ""
"**Match Arrow field names exactly.** The bridge validates that Arrow struct "
"field names match the ROS2 message definition. Missing fields use default "
"values (zero for numbers, empty string). Extra fields cause an error."
msgstr ""

#: src/advanced/ros2-bridge.md:873
msgid ""
"**Use explicit `output`/`input` in multi-topic mode.** Default ID mapping "
"(stripping `/`, replacing `/` with `_`) can be confusing for deep topic "
"names. Explicit IDs make the dataflow YAML self-documenting."
msgstr ""

#: src/advanced/ros2-bridge.md:875
msgid ""
"**Set QoS to match the ROS2 publisher/subscriber.** QoS mismatches (e.g., "
"reliable subscriber with best-effort publisher) cause silent communication "
"failures. Check with `ros2 topic info -v /topic_name` to see the existing "
"QoS settings."
msgstr ""

#: src/advanced/ros2-bridge.md:877
msgid ""
"**Pass through `request_id` in service responses.** The bridge correlates "
"responses to requests using the `request_id` metadata parameter. If the "
"handler does not include `request_id` in the response metadata, the bridge "
"cannot match the response to the original ROS2 request."
msgstr ""

#: src/advanced/ws-control.md:3
msgid ""
"Dora's control plane uses WebSocket connections for all communication "
"between the CLI, coordinator, and daemons. A single Axum server exposes "
"three routes on one port, replacing the previous multi-port TCP design. JSON "
"text frames carry a UUID-correlated request-reply protocol with "
"fire-and-forget events for log streaming."
msgstr ""

#: src/advanced/ws-control.md:7
